description.narrative: (Ethiopia): The Strengthening Ethiopia's Urban Health Program (SEUHP) aims at improving the health status of Ethiopia's urban population by reducing the incidence of Tuberculosis (TB), HIV, maternal, neonatal and child morbidity and mortality through improved quality, use, and management of urban health services. The Government of Ethiopia's Urban Health Extension Program engages more than 5,000 nurses to provide household-centered health promotion, disease prevention, and limited curative services in urban areas. In FY 2017, SEUHP will continue to enhance family health, hygiene and sanitation, maternal neonatal and child health services; strengthen health systems in 49 urban areas; train and supervise urban health extension workers; support long and short-term family planning referral services, community-based immunization, HIV testing, anti-natal care referrals and defaulter tracing, postpartum care, and TB screening and referrals.
